They also agreed to stop administering them.

00:45:28.976 --> 00:45:31.145
Then we'll end up taking the fall for it.

00:45:32.688 --> 00:45:35.441
And not a single person will step up to protect us.

00:45:39.403 --> 00:45:40.988
- Dr. Hyeon. - How strange.

00:45:41.781 --> 00:45:45.117
You normally play it by the book, but you're making an exception here.

00:45:46.035 --> 00:45:48.870
This is clearly an illegal medical practice.

00:45:48.871 --> 00:45:51.123
If you won't report her, I will.

00:46:01.759 --> 00:46:02.927
Dr. Do.

00:46:05.263 --> 00:46:06.430
Oh

00:46:30.830 --> 00:46:32.623
Why is it so cold?

00:46:36.460 --> 00:46:38.044
You'll get better in no time.

00:46:38.045 --> 00:46:41.716
Goodness, thank you.

00:46:44.927 --> 00:46:48.431
JINEONDO VILLAGE HALL

00:47:07.158 --> 00:47:09.243
You reported her?

00:47:10.661 --> 00:47:13.705
Despite everything I told you!

00:47:13.706 --> 00:47:19.795
It's not like you'll come to us every time someone gets sick!

00:47:20.880 --> 00:47:24.966
Are you going to be here every other day,

00:47:24.967 --> 00:47:28.220
Every time we're staring death in the eye?

00:47:29.013 --> 00:47:31.973
It's not like you ever did anything for us!

00:47:31.974 --> 00:47:35.727
What were you doing as my son lay dying?

00:47:35.728 --> 00:47:41.359
What were you doing?

00:47:44.862 --> 00:47:47.114
Seonu!

00:47:47.823 --> 00:47:50.242
Seonu!

00:47:54.372 --> 00:47:57.458
Seonu!

00:47:59.251 --> 00:48:01.420
What were you doing? :cue

00:48:02.505 --> 00:48:04.839
What have you ever done?

00:48:04.840 --> 00:48:07.133
What did any of you do for us?

00:48:07.134 --> 00:48:09.887
What did you do for us?

00:48:14.308 --> 00:48:15.309
Stop it, sir.

00:48:16.352 --> 00:48:17.937
I was the one who reported her.

00:48:18.729 --> 00:48:20.897
It was the best thing for the residents.

00:48:50.553 --> 00:48:52.721
Did you have to do it?

00:48:55.266 --> 00:48:57.852
We could have looked for a different solution.

00:49:00.521 --> 00:49:01.689
What other solution?

00:49:03.232 --> 00:49:05.567
You mean letting anyone stick needles into people

00:49:05.568 --> 00:49:07.820
Because they have no access to a doctor?

00:49:12.241 --> 00:49:15.911
Sure, doing as the residents say might make things easier for us now,

00:49:16.495 --> 00:49:19.540
But when something really bad happens, the blame will fall on us.

00:49:21.667 --> 00:49:24.586
And when that happens, we won't be able to protect them,

00:49:24.587 --> 00:49:26.130
Or ourselves.

00:49:27.631 --> 00:49:31.135
Why are you taking this so personally, Dr. Do?

00:49:36.223 --> 00:49:38.434
It's because I know how scary it can be

00:49:41.812 --> 00:49:44.148
To have no one around to help when you need it.

00:50:21.810 --> 00:50:24.521
If you have something to say, just say it.

00:50:24.522 --> 00:50:26.815
Instead of following me around like that.

00:50:28.359 --> 00:50:29.360
I'm sorry.

00:50:38.327 --> 00:50:40.662
Did I or did I not ask you to give me some time?

00:50:40.663 --> 00:50:42.789
How could you do that to me?

00:50:42.790 --> 00:50:45.792
What kind of person do you take me for, that you couldn't even wait

00:50:45.793 --> 00:50:48.253
Before you decided to jump to such a gross conclusion?

00:50:48.254 --> 00:50:51.131
Why couldn't you trust me?

00:50:56.887 --> 00:51:00.015
It wasn't because I couldn't trust you.

00:51:00.849 --> 00:51:02.560
It's because I was afraid.

00:51:04.019 --> 00:51:07.356
I was afraid you might like someone else more than you like me.

00:51:10.651 --> 00:51:12.695
I was so pathetic.

00:51:16.574 --> 00:51:18.325
I'm so scared, you see.

00:51:20.995 --> 00:51:23.289
I like you so much

00:51:24.498 --> 00:51:27.459
And I'm scared you're going to like someone else more than me. :cue

00:51:29.211 --> 00:51:30.379
But you see

00:51:33.007 --> 00:51:35.342
I know this is going to sound really pathetic,

00:51:36.802 --> 00:51:39.513
But let me make just one more pathetic request.

00:51:40.889 --> 00:51:42.308
Please forgive me.

00:51:45.102 --> 00:51:47.521
I can't break up with you, Ms. Eom.

00:51:49.273 --> 00:51:50.274
Okay?

00:51:51.650 --> 00:51:53.819
Just give me one last chance.

00:52:02.369 --> 00:52:04.788
I'm way more pathetic than you.

00:52:07.750 --> 00:52:10.335
I also kept it from you because I was scared.

00:52:10.336 --> 00:52:14.256
I don't know why I get so embarrassed about everything when I'm around you.

00:52:15.466 --> 00:52:17.968
I was worried that you might judge me for it.

00:52:19.136 --> 00:52:20.721
Don't say that.

00:52:22.389 --> 00:52:24.390
Because it's all my fault.

00:52:24.391 --> 00:52:28.354
It's all my fault.

00:52:30.564 --> 00:52:32.106
Oh, yeah.

00:52:32.107 --> 00:52:33.776
Jiung left.

00:52:35.694 --> 00:52:36.695
What?

00:52:37.529 --> 00:52:40.699
I'm saying I'm all alone at home now.

00:52:41.408 --> 00:52:42.743
Uh

00:52:45.621 --> 00:52:49.583
Does that mean you forgive me?

00:52:51.043 --> 00:52:52.836
Do I have to spell it out for you?

00:52:58.133 --> 00:52:59.385
You mean it?

00:53:02.096 --> 00:53:04.014
Oh, and that.

00:53:12.815 --> 00:53:14.817
What's this?

00:53:16.652 --> 00:53:18.736
Can't you tell?

00:53:18.737 --> 00:53:20.823
I stitched it up for you.

00:53:24.451 --> 00:53:25.869
Ms. Eom.

00:53:27.121 --> 00:53:30.124
Just how long were you going to wear a shirt with a hole in it?

00:53:32.251 --> 00:53:33.418
And no more crying!

00:53:36.547 --> 00:53:37.798
Thank you.

00:53:45.305 --> 00:53:46.890
I love you, Ms. Eom.

00:54:06.952 --> 00:54:11.164
He looked downcast all day, so I told him he could clock out early.

00:54:11.165 --> 00:54:13.584
Oh, I see.

00:54:14.084 --> 00:54:18.921
By the way, why is Dr. Jiui so obsessed with Jineondo anyway?

00:54:18.922 --> 00:54:22.384
It's not like we could let them keep operating an illegal pharmacy.

00:54:22.968 --> 00:54:26.804
Gosh, just when you think you know someone.

00:54:26.805 --> 00:54:28.598
I mean, normally,

00:54:28.599 --> 00:54:31.685
He's such a stickler for the rules who plays it by the book.

00:54:33.771 --> 00:54:34.980
I just don't get him.

00:54:35.481 --> 00:54:39.484
I don't get him at all.

00:54:39.485 --> 00:54:41.487
:cue

00:55:55.018 --> 00:55:57.854
Captain, he's going to die! Please go faster!

00:55:58.855 --> 00:56:03.109
Seonu!

00:56:03.110 --> 00:56:04.194
Seonu.

00:56:06.321 --> 00:56:08.239
I'm not getting a pulse.

00:56:11.326 --> 00:56:12.327
Seonu!

00:56:13.078 --> 00:56:14.329
Seonu!

00:56:45.235 --> 00:56:46.278
Oh, Ms. Yuk.

00:56:57.748 --> 00:57:02.085
Winter sure seems to arrive early on an island.

00:57:08.550 --> 00:57:11.386
You don't have to put on a brave face for me.

00:57:16.725 --> 00:57:19.311
I know you're struggling a lot.

00:57:24.358 --> 00:57:26.902
You were always by my side.

00:57:29.071 --> 00:57:32.157
So I also want to be by your side.

00:57:33.909 --> 00:57:38.330
But I'm afraid that if I'm not careful, I'll end up hurting you.

00:57:45.170 --> 00:57:47.172
Can you tell me about what happened?

00:57:51.760 --> 00:57:53.804
So you don't have to harbor it alone.

00:58:00.602 --> 00:58:02.688
I don't think we deserve to be happy.

00:58:08.402 --> 00:58:10.404
That wouldn't be fair to Seonu. :cue

00:59:00.495 --> 00:59:02.205
I don't think I can do it.

00:59:18.805 --> 00:59:20.974
I don't think I can keep doing this either.

00:59:23.685 --> 00:59:27.062
I'm done sitting on the sidelines while you suffer.

00:59:27.063 --> 00:59:28.940
I'm not going to leave you alone.

00:59:30.817 --> 00:59:32.611
Because that's what you did for me.

00:59:37.115 --> 00:59:38.575
So please

00:59:45.665 --> 00:59:47.751
Lean on me.

01:01:21.011 --> 01:01:23.888
IT'S NOT YOU I HATED

01:01:23.889 --> 01:01:30.645
I THINK I HATED MYSELF

01:01:39.821 --> 01:01:43.074
COME ON, TAKE A DIP WITH ME

01:01:51.917 --> 01:01:53.417
FILMING OUT ON THE WATER MEANS

01:01:53.418 --> 01:01:55.086
THERE'S NOWHERE TO HIDE FROM THE SUN

01:01:59.174 --> 01:02:02.093
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

01:02:02.761 --> 01:02:04.846
A PH doc on medication?

01:02:05.722 --> 01:02:08.974
I was kind of hoping to get examined by a different doctor.

01:02:08.975 --> 01:02:10.601
Dr. Do Jiui!

01:02:10.602 --> 01:02:13.229
I can't take this anymore.

01:02:13.772 --> 01:02:15.606
I'm here to meet Jiui.

01:02:15.607 --> 01:02:16.983
Dr. Do Jiui?

01:02:18.735 --> 01:02:21.029
I know Jiui better than anyone else.

01:02:21.613 --> 01:02:23.782
That's what I wanted to hear from you most.

01:02:25.659 --> 01:02:28.453
Please convince him to leave this island.

01:02:31.665 --> 01:02:33.667
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park

